      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six power plant, delivering a 7,900 RPM redline through individual throttle bodies. This example is equipped with the tactile Getrag six-speed manual transmission and a factory limited-slip differential. Recent preventative maintenance includes a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring structural integrity under high lateral loads. The suspension retains its original geometry with refreshed bushings, providing the precise turn-in and communicative feedback these chassis are known for. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with spirited use, the mechanical synchronicity between the dual-overhead cams and the high-pressure oiling system remains impeccable. A true enthusiast's specimen optimized for peak volumetric efficiency and corner-exit traction.",
